📍Total Tease!!📍 For the past few weeks I've been testing the @covergirl Total Tease Mascara! My husband purchase mine from our local @walgreens. It comes in Both Regular & WaterProof Formulas. •
•
📌Claims according to CG Website:Total Tease Mascara darkens and thickens lashes for maximum lash definition. Tease with ease for ultimate lash separation with our smudge defying formula. Our specialized detailing tip allows for no-mess targeted application and gives you a precision tease just where you need it. .
.
📌The wand + mini review: As you can see from the picture, the wand can be a little intimidating but don't worry, it is super easy to use. I do admit, the first time using it, I had to concentrate to make sure I didn't poke my eyeball out! 😂😂 Okay, the Brush, which is labeled as Brush 1 is great for building up volume. I normally do 2 coats max but you can build up to your liking. Brush 2 is perfect for getting those stubborn lashes that are hard to get. For me, it's usually the inner and outer lashes. I have a hard time getting those! You can also use the tip (brush 2) to define and get rid of any clumps that have may have build up! Oh and may I also add that the tip is perfect for the bottom lashes 😻😻 Overall, I Love this mascara! It does the job and it doesn't smudge or flake, at least not on me. I love how it separates and defines my lashes + love the volume it gives them. I would definitely  repurchase again and do recommend it! If you're looking for a mascara that offers great volume, without clumping+ added definition then this is for you!  Also, let me know if you like these type of reviews, or is the eyeball a little too much for you?! Lol I hope this was helpful and if you have any questions, leave them in the comments. 💋 •
